{"title":"RIPng with Cisco & ISS","date":"2022-10-19T16:00:00.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"Oct 20, 2022","L":"10/20/2022","MM-DD":"10-20"},"link":"2022/10/20/ripng-cisco-iss","tags":["L3","cisco","networking","routing","routing protocol"],"categories":["networking"],"updated":"2022-10-19T16:00:00.000Z","content":"<blockquote>\n<p>IPv6 RIP functions the same and offers the same benefits as RIP in IPv4. RIP enhancements for IPv6, detailed in RFC 2080, include support for IPv6 addresses and prefixes, and the use of the all-RIP-devices multicast group address FF02::9 as the destination address for RIP update messages.  – Cisco</p>\n</blockquote>\n<span id=\"more\"></span>\n<h2 id=\"cisco-command\">cisco command<a title=\"#cisco-command\" href=\"#cisco-command\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"enable\">enable<a title=\"#enable\" href=\"#enable\"></a></h3>\n<figure class=\"highlight plaintext\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"># configure terminal</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">(config)# ipv6 unicast-routing</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">(config)# interface __type__ __number__</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">(config-if)# ipv6 rip __name__ enable</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<p>where the <strong>name</strong> is the <code>process name</code> for rip</p>\n<h3 id=\"customizing-ipv6-rip-(optional)\">customizing IPv6 RIP (optional)<a title=\"#customizing-ipv6-rip-(optional)\" href=\"#customizing-ipv6-rip-(optional)\"></a></h3>\n<figure class=\"highlight plaintext\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br><span class=\"line\">9</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"># configure terminal</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">#### optional-1</span><br><span class=\"line\">(config)# interface __type__ __number__</span><br><span class=\"line\">(config-if)# ipv6 rip __name__  default-information &#123;only | originate&#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\">#### optional-2</span><br><span class=\"line\">(config)# ipv6 router rip __name__</span><br><span class=\"line\">(config-router)# maximum-paths __number-paths__</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<p>ref: <a href=\"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/iproute_rip/configuration/xe-3s/asr1000/ip6-rip-xe.html\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/iproute_rip/configuration/xe-3s/asr1000/ip6-rip-xe.html</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"iss-command\">ISS command<a title=\"#iss-command\" href=\"#iss-command\"></a></h2>\n<div class=\"φbq\"><div class=\"φbs\"><table><thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Command</th>\n<th>Check</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>ipv6 router rip</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div></div>","prev":{"title":"IPv6","link":"2022/10/20/ipv6"},"next":{"title":"Python Execution Timer with Decorator","link":"2022/10/19/python-execution-timer-with-decorator"},"plink":"https://jason19970210.github.io/2022/10/20/ripng-cisco-iss/","toc":[{"id":"cisco-command","title":"cisco command","index":"1","children":[{"id":"enable","title":"enable","index":"1.1"},{"id":"customizing-ipv6-rip-(optional)","title":"customizing IPv6 RIP (optional)","index":"1.2"}]},{"id":"iss-command","title":"ISS command","index":"2"}],"reading_time":"158 words in 1 min"}